# Edge-to-edge pages, no full-screen card wrappers

The page chrome IS the card. Wrapping the whole route in a `rounded-2xl border …`
container makes the app feel like a website-inside-a-website and wastes
horizontal space on mobile. It's banned.

## Rules

1. The top-level template of any `pages/**/*.vue` file MUST NOT be a single
   `rounded-* border …` element. Use `AppPageContent` + `moh-gutter-x` and
   let sections breathe to the viewport edge.
2. Section separators use `border-b moh-border` (or a subtle shadow), not a
   nested rounded card around the whole section.
3. Lists / feeds / carousels: each row may have its own surface treatment,
   but the list itself must not be wrapped in an outer rounded card.
4. Individual cards are fine when they ARE the unit (a single composer card,
   a single empty-state card, a single CTA tile). They are not fine when they
   contain "the whole page".
5. On mobile, content should reach the viewport edge wherever it improves
   density (carousels, media, feed rows). Use `moh-gutter-x` for text blocks
   and form fields.

## Quick check before merging

- [ ] Open the page on mobile width. Is there visible empty space to the
      LEFT and RIGHT of the page's content? If yes, the wrapper card has
      to go.
- [ ] Is there exactly one outer `rounded-* border` ancestor around 80%+ of
      the page body? If yes, remove it.

If you genuinely need a "card-shaped page" (e.g. an auth form), it should be
narrow and centered (`max-w-md mx-auto`), not full-width.

## Example

Bad — full-screen card wraps the entire page:

```vue
<template>
  <AppPageContent>
    <div class="rounded-2xl border moh-border moh-surface m-3 p-4">
      <h1>Some page</h1>
      <!-- everything else nested inside -->
    </div>
  </AppPageContent>
</template>
```

Good — edge-to-edge with section dividers:

```vue
<template>
  <AppPageContent>
    <div class="moh-gutter-x border-b moh-border pt-4 pb-4">
      <h1 class="moh-h1">Some page</h1>
    </div>
    <section class="border-b moh-border py-5">
      <!-- carousel reaches the viewport edge; cards inside use the gutter -->
    </section>
    <section>
      <div class="moh-gutter-x py-5">…</div>
    </section>
  </AppPageContent>
</template>
```
